defaultNone of the NLSA boroughs has a sufficient supply of in-house foster carers to care for all the children within their boroughs who require
default placements, nor is this a question purely of numbers. Sometimes in order to find a good match for a young person a very specialist family needs to be found. This specialism may relate to cultural or religious needs or may be to do with specialist skills i
defaultn handling disabilities or emotionally challenging behaviour.
