defaultNLSA has recently undertaken a commissioning exercise to stimulate the market and increase the number of ind
defaultependent fostering placements available in our sub-region
default. This has come about because we recognise that in order to provide an attractive level of business for providers we are stronger if we work together. This is particularly the case where we are looki
defaultng for specialist placements where the needs group are low incidence, for example with certain disabilities or placements for young people on remand. For this reason t
defaulthe tendering exercise has been undertaken in partnership with a further 5 boroughs across
default East London. We are currently in the process of evaluating the bids received and in January 2014 we hope to sign contracts with around 50 agencies to provide approximately 1000 foster placements annually across north and east London. 
